    "is_free": true,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Apricity is a top-down shooter designed to be played with friends. </p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Heat System</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >When you deal damage, you build Heat, and at 100% Heat you become HOT, increasing your attack speed. After a few seconds of not dealing damage, your Heat drops to 0 almost instantly. Reloading (reloading is just the term for a special action, you can fire your primary weapon infinitely) conserves Heat and recharges your abilities, unless you are injured, in which case your Heat is expended to rapidly heal you.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Importantly, enemies drop orbs on death that heal you and recharge your abilities, often forcing players into a choice: do I back off and reload, or just keep shooting and hope I can heal from the orb?</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Classes</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Apricity has 11 character classes. Each class has a different weapon, passive, and two activated abilities.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Classes interact with each enemy type and item differently, and each class has a special relationship with the Heat system.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Gamemodes</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Apricity has two gamemodes. The first is Adventure, in which players make choices in a text adventure in between combats. Winning combats equals success in the text adventure. The ultimate goal is to destroy Catrapos.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The second is Endless, a simple but fun score attack mode that appeals more to singleplayer users.</p>",
